==English==
{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
From Japanese [[連濁]] (rendaku), ''sequential voicing''.

===Noun===
'''rendaku'''
#{{linguistics}} In the [[Japanese]] language, a phenomenon which governs the [[voicing]] of the initial [[consonant]] of the non-initial portion of a [[compound]] or [[prefix]]ed word. An example is [[時々]], where the second element "-toki" becomes "-doki".

===Synonyms===
*[[sequential voicing]]